      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "> I think the ideal API would define a serialized recoverable signature to be a 65-byte string and simply take care of parsing the first byte. Maybe we can simply add a function that does this but also the keep the current function as it is?\n\nUnfortunately, no caller would be interested in such a function I think. The recoverable signatures used for message signatures use 65-byte signatures, but the first byte is \"27 + recid + 4*pubkey_is_compressed\".\n\nSo unless we intend to move the full exact scheme as used there into libsecp256k1, I don't think there is much actionable here.",
